<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,684,1466]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,283,1188,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Note:—</emphasis>
This species is characterized by pseudisidia with many projecting hyphae and the presence of norstictic acid as a major secondary metabolite. 
<taxonomicName authority="Jagadeesh (2014: 40)" authorityName="Jagadeesh" authorityPageNumber="40" authorityYear="2014" box="[551,1070,1224,1250]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="coralloides">
<emphasis box="[551,832,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Herpothallon coralloides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M." box="[837,1070,1224,1250]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" pagination="39 - 49" refId="ref3995" refString="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M., (2014) The genus Herpothallon (Arthoniaceae) in the Andaman Islands, India. The Lichenologist 46 (1): 39 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0024282913000571" type="journal article" year="2014">Jagadeesh (2014: 40)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is also pseudoisidiate and contains norstictic acid, but it has a pale green to whitish grey thallus that also contains confluentic acid and much larger pseudisidia (up to 1.0 × 
<quantity box="[407,487,1296,1322]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1mm</quantity>
) that are felty, but without projecting hyphae (
<bibRefCitation author="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M." box="[1007,1191,1296,1322]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" pagination="39 - 49" refId="ref3995" refString="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M., (2014) The genus Herpothallon (Arthoniaceae) in the Andaman Islands, India. The Lichenologist 46 (1): 39 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0024282913000571" type="journal article" year="2014">Jagadeesh 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The morphologically most similar species is 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fee) Frisch &amp; G. Thor (2010: 290)" authorityName="Frisch &amp; G. Thor" authorityPageNumber="290" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Fee" box="[401,1024,1332,1358]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Crypthonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="albida">
